Until now, I have benefited from contacts that I have obtained through the competitions.
The franchise sale of his hotel helped Lukas Pytloun to win the Best Individual Entrepreneur competition.
The winner of last year's Best Individual Entrepreneur competition was 28-year-old entrepreneur Lukas Pytloun.
His adventure to success is like in a movie.
Lukas Pytloun liked to travel.
And abroad, he realized that in Libérec there was missing a quality accommodation site at a reasonable price.
From his savings on what he had earned when he worked abroad and with the help of a bank loan he bought a small building of 5 apartments half demolished.
Knowing that he was still a student in the third year of higher education, it was a courageous action.
"The relationship between quality and price of accommodation in our region has made me want to do something," says Pytloun.
He began to rent the first apartment rebuilt to foreign workers.
He reinvested the profit in the building that he converted into a pension with 54 beds.
Since then, his entrepreneurial activity has allowed him to open 4 pensions, two style restaurants and two hotels with a total capacity of nearly 300 beds of all categories of accommodation.
