The victory brought him more popularity and to be known in Libérec and its surroundings.
"People recognized me on the streets, congratulated me often and, I must say, it was very pleasant," he recalls.
It recommends participation in this competition to all those who are trying to do something.
It is not necessary to win, but any opportunity to be visible is good.
He says he's been using his contacts and knowledge until now that he couldn't have gotten in any other way.
"With those I met through the contest I started to maintain business relations regularly.
According to him, the reputation associated with success also had an impact on employees.
And he's got about 70.
"I observe at home above all the loyalty and pride of being engaged in something that has been generally recognized."
