I wish my successor a better year than we had in Farmet.
The euphoria of victory was quickly replaced by the effects of the crisis.
Thanks to the goal of the winner Farmet has the worst moments behind him.
The one who came to pick up the prize in Slovansky dum for the first place of the competition for the Firm of the year organized by Vodaphone last year is Karel Zdarsky the owner of the company Farmet.
The jury rewarded the efforts with which it transformed a tool shop in Ceska Skalice into a firm with turnover of 100 million crowns.
"I can say that the award not only encouraged me, my colleagues and increased our confidence in ourselves to fight against competition," said the winner of last year's competition today.
At the beginning of Farmet's history there was a desire to do something useful.
And so when the state offered Karel Zdrasky's father to rent the small workshop as compensation after the communists confiscated the property, he did not hesitate long, refused a career in a firm where he worked at the time, and created a company with some comrades in his father's surroundings for the manufacture of plastic baths.
Not very long after they began to specialize in vegetable oil presses.
After 18 years it has become the largest manufacturer of automatic presses in Central Europe.
The company was known even to the non-specialized public after the success of the competition through the media.
"Not only did our customers really get to know the Farmet brand better, but also the foreign partners who started to realize that they were collaborating with a company that got the greatest success in its country of origin," says Karel Zdarsky.
But the past year has not happened at Farmet only in the euphoria of victory.
The valuation of the company was based on the economic results of 2008 and part of 2009.
